#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.88"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.88:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.88:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.88:0.3"
msgid "88. Therasutta"
msgstr "88. Senior Mendicants"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.88:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanaahitāya "
"paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya ahitāya dukkhāya "
"devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the "
"hurt and unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of "
"gods and humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.115"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.88:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.88:2.2"
msgid "Thero hoti rattaññū cirapabbajito;"
msgstr "They are senior and have long gone forth."

#. VAR: sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ → gahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.88:2.3"
msgid "ñāto hoti yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro;"
msgstr ""
"They’re well-known, famous, with a large following that includes both "
"laypeople and renunciates."

msgctxt "an5.88:2.4"
msgid "lābhī hoti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the "
"sick."

# See BB’s note for variant.
#. VAR: appaṭividdhā → suppaṭividdhā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.88:2.5"
msgid ""
"bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti, tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā appaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"understanding them with view."

msgctxt "an5.88:2.6"
msgid ""
"micchādiṭṭhiko hoti viparītadassano, so bahujanaṃ saddhammā vuṭṭhāpetvā "
"asaddhamme patiṭṭhāpeti."
msgstr ""
"But they have wrong view and distorted perspective. They draw many people "
"away from the true teaching and establish them in false teachings."

msgctxt "an5.88:2.7"
msgid ""
"Thero bhikkhu rattaññū cirapabbajito itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, ñāto "
"thero bhikkhu yasassī sagahaṭṭhapabbajitānaṃ bahujanaparivāro itipissa "
"diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, lābhī thero bhikkhu "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ itipissa "
"diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti, bahussuto thero bhikkhu sutadharo sutasannicayo "
"itipissa diṭṭhānugatiṃ āpajjanti."
msgstr ""
"People follow their example, thinking that the senior mendicant is senior "
"and has long gone forth. Or that they’re well-known, famous, with a large "
"following that includes both laypeople and renunciates. Or that they receive "
"robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick. Or that "
"they’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned."

msgctxt "an5.88:2.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu "
"bahujanaahitāya paṭipanno hoti bahujanaasukhāya bahuno janassa anatthāya "
"ahitāya dukkhāya devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant who has these five qualities is acting for the hurt and "
"unhappiness of the people, for the harm, hurt, and suffering of gods and "
"humans."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.88:3.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato thero bhikkhu bahujanahitāya "
"paṭipanno hoti bahujanasukhāya bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya "
"devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A senior mendicant who has five qualities is acting for the welfare and "
"happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and "
"humans."

#. </p><p>
